parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition module can cause the engine to stall or die, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded, especially when driving at high speeds.
symptoms: the vehicle dies at any time or place
the ignition switch and steering column get hot
the ignition key becomes hot and difficult to hold or remove.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Oil leaks from the intake manifold can cause engine damage, leading to costly repairs and potentially causing accidents due to engine failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A defective computer/ECU can cause unusual behavior, such as increased power when pressing the brakes, which can lead to accidents or loss of control.

symptoms: The ignition switch becomes excessively hot

the vehicle pulls to one side while steering
